The paper discusses the architecture and performance analysis of a distributed antenna system, which involves communication and signal processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the fundamental limits of communication and information processing. The paper also involves networked systems and wireless communication, which are relevant to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The analysis of the system's performance and optimization can be related to cs.SY (Systems and Control), while the use of multiple antennas and signal processing can be related to cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper discusses the use of low-resolution ADCs, which can be related to cs.AR (Hardware Architecture).
